    behavioral="• Emphasize that compliance is a business enabler, not a hindrance — protects firm reputation and client trust\n• Discuss how you stay current: SEC no-action letters, industry roundtables, compliance conferences\n• Show understanding of fiduciary standard vs suitability standard (higher standard for advisers)\n• Demonstrate experience with compliance testing: trade surveillance, email review, marketing materials approval\n• Mention the importance of a strong compliance culture set by senior management",
